    "notes": "CachyOS - EAC installs and downloads successfully, but launcher still fails with Unexpected error (#1)\n\nSystem:\n- CachyOS\n- AMD GPU\n- Steam Linux client\n- Proton Easy Anti-Cheat Runtime installed\n\nTested:\n- Cleared Steam cache\n- Verified files\n- Reinstalled game\n- Wiped compatdata\n- Reinstalled / reinitialized EAC\n- Confirmed EAC EOS folder exists in prefix\n\nLog findings:\n- service.log shows EAC install completed successfully\n- loader.log shows EAC connected to Epic\u2019s module CDN and received HTTP 200\n- anticheatlauncher.log reaches 100% and then exits with:\n  Launcher finished with: 210, 'Unexpected error. (#1)'\n- loader.log ends with:\n  [EAC Callback] Code: 509. Message: 'Unexpected error. (#1)'\n\nConclusion:\nThis is not a cache issue and not a missing EAC install. In my case EAC bootstrap completes, downloads the Linux module, and then fails at the final validation / handoff stage. Looks like a Proton/EAC/BattleBit compatibility regression rather than a normal local install problem.\n\nNotes:\n- BattleBit on Linux appears inconsistent recently\n- Try Proton 9.0 (Beta), Proton Hotfix, and GE-Proton before Experimental\n- Disable Gamescope / MangoHUD for testing",
